In [75]:
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns

Store By FootFall¶

In [76]:
footfall_by_location = df.groupby('store_location')['transaction_id'].count().sort_values(ascending=False)
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
sns.barplot(x=footfall_by_location.index, y=footfall_by_location.values, palette='rainbow')
plt.title('Footfall by Store Location')
plt.xlabel('Store Location')
plt.ylabel('Footfall')
plt.xticks(rotation=45)
plt.show()
